[Student "S"]
{SOUTH might jump-shift, but with no 5-card suit prefers to use Jacoby 2NT.

NORTH shows some extra strength plus a 5-card \C suit with his 4\C bid. 

When SOUTH's Blackwood discovers two Aces in NORTH's hand she goes right to 7\S. 
She knows NORTH has only three red cards and her \HA 
\D A K will take care of them. She figures NORTH can ruff 
out any \C losers.}

